
Overview of verb glorify

The verb glorify has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (4) laud, extol, exalt, glorify, proclaim -- (praise, glorify, or honor; "extol the virtues of one's children"; "glorify one's spouse's cooking")
2. (1) glorify -- (bestow glory upon; "The victory over the enemy glorified the Republic")
3. transfigure, glorify, spiritualize -- (elevate or idealize, in allusion to Christ's transfiguration)
4. glorify -- (cause to seem more splendid; "You are glorifying a rather mediocre building")
